ATTRIBUTIONS:

This project uses concepts and methodologies from:

1. PRIMM (Predict, Run, Investigate, Modify, Make)
   - Sentance et al. (2019)
   - https://blogs.kcl.ac.uk/cser/2019/01/18/primm-a-structured-approach-to-teaching-programming/

2. Parson Problems
   - Parsons, D., & Haden, P. (2006)
   - https://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/~ddgarcia/papers/p99-parsons.pdf

3. CS Unplugged - "Programming Languages" Activity
   - Tim Bell, Ian H. Witten, Mike Fellows
   - University of Canterbury
   - https://csunplugged.org/

4. Olympiad Problems (Level 2)
   - LeetCode problems #1, #9, #70
   - https://leetcode.com/

5. Educational Content Generation
   - Created with assistance from Claude Code by Anthropic
   - https://claude.ai/code

================================================================================

This educational material was developed for the "Digital Literacy and AI Fundamentals" course at inVision U.
